To check a particular GMPI ID—for example, the user-story example 706163978—run these queries.
1. Check the current view output
SELECT *
FROM ASQN_PRD_ORCHESTRATION_DB.REPORT.VW_WM_UHC_MBR_PREF_RPT
WHERE GMPI_ID = 706163978
ORDER BY REPORT_MONTH DESC;
This shows how many rows and report months currently appear for that GMPI.
2. Check all source report months
SELECT
    DM.GMPI_ID,
    DM.MEMBER_ID,
    MRM.REPORT_MONTH,
    MRM.MEMBER_FIRST_NAME,
    MRM.MEMBER_LAST_NAME
FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.DIM_MEMBER DM
INNER JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.MEMBER_REPORT_MONTH MRM
    ON DM.MEMBER_ID = MRM.MEMBER_ID
WHERE DM.GMPI_ID = 706163978
ORDER BY MRM.REPORT_MONTH DESC;
This displays every available membership month for that GMPI.
3. Check the overall latest report month
SELECT MAX(REPORT_MONTH) AS CURRENT_REPORT_MONTH
FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.MEMBER_REPORT_MONTH;
Compare this result with the report months for GMPI 706163978.
4. Verify whether the member is active in the current month
SELECT
    DM.GMPI_ID,
    DM.MEMBER_ID,
    MRM.REPORT_MONTH
FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.DIM_MEMBER DM
INNER JOIN FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.MEMBER_REPORT_MONTH MRM
    ON DM.MEMBER_ID = MRM.MEMBER_ID
WHERE DM.GMPI_ID = 706163978
  AND MRM.REPORT_MONTH = (
      SELECT MAX(REPORT_MONTH)
      FROM FWRB_PRD_WMIDR_DB.BI_ANALYSIS.MEMBER_REPORT_MONTH
  );
Interpret the result:
A row is returned: GMPI is present in the current report month.
No row is returned: GMPI’s membership is from an older month, so the corrected view should exclude it.
5. Check for multiple rows in the view
SELECT
    GMPI_ID,
    COUNT(*) AS ROW_COUNT,
    COUNT(DISTINCT REPORT_MONTH) AS REPORT_MONTH_COUNT,
    MIN(REPORT_MONTH) AS EARLIEST_REPORT_MONTH,
    MAX(REPORT_MONTH) AS LATEST_REPORT_MONTH
FROM ASQN_PRD_ORCHESTRATION_DB.REPORT.VW_WM_UHC_MBR_PREF_RPT
WHERE GMPI_ID = 706163978
GROUP BY GMPI_ID;
If REPORT_MONTH_COUNT is greater than 1, that GMPI appears across multiple report months.




